1. App Overview

Purpose

The GHL Farmer App enables hemp farmers to:
- Enroll their plots in the carbon credit program
- Monitor carbon capture progress in real-time
- Track earnings from verified carbon credits
- Manage sensors and receive alerts
- Get paid directly to their bank account

Key Principle: Hide the Crypto

The app abstracts all blockchain complexity. Farmers see:
- Euros, not tokens
- "Verified carbon" not "minted credits"
- "Earnings" not "wallet balance"
- "Bank transfer" not "fiat offramp"

The blockchain is infrastructure, invisible to the user.

Target Platforms

- iOS 14+ (iPhone 8 and newer)
- Android 10+ (API level 29)
- React Native for cross-platform development
- Offline-first architecture with background sync

---

2. User Personas

Persona 1: Jean-Pierre (Primary)

Profile:
- Age: 58
- Location: Aube, France (La Chanvriere member)
- Farm: 75 hectares, hemp for 12 years
- Tech comfort: Low - uses smartphone for calls, WhatsApp, weather
- Language: French

Goals:
- Earn extra income with minimal effort
- Understand what's happening on his land
- Not deal with complicated technology

Frustrations:
- Small text, complex interfaces
- Apps that don't work in rural areas
- Too many steps to do simple things

Quote: "I grow hemp. I don't need to understand carbon markets to get paid for it."

Persona 2: Anna (Secondary)

Profile:
- Age: 34
- Location: Brandenburg, Germany
- Farm: 120 hectares, new to hemp (2 years)
- Tech comfort: Medium - manages farm accounting on tablet
- Language: German, English

Goals:
- Track farm performance with data
- Maximize revenue from carbon program
- Understand verification process

Frustrations:
- Lack of transparency in how credits are calculated
- Waiting for payments without status updates

Quote: "Show me the data and when I get paid."

Persona 3: Hans (Tertiary - No Smartphone)

Profile:
- Age: 67
- Location: Zeeland, Netherlands
- Farm: 45 hectares, hemp cooperative member
- Tech comfort: Very low - feature phone only
- Language: Dutch

Goals:
- Participate without changing behavior
- Get notifications about important events
- Have someone to call if there's a problem

Frustrations:
- Being excluded from digital programs
- Missing important information

Quote: "Just tell me when there's money and if something's wrong."

---

3. Design Principles

3.1 Simplicity First

- One primary action per screen
- Maximum 3 taps to any destination
- No jargon - farm language, not tech language
- Progressive disclosure - details on demand

3.2 Offline-First Architecture

- All data cached locally
- Actions queued when offline
- Clear offline indicator
- Graceful degradation
- Background sync when connected

3.3 Accessibility by Default

- Minimum 48x48dp touch targets
- WCAG AA contrast ratios
- Large text support (16sp minimum)
- Screen reader compatibility
- Reduced motion option

3.4 Trust Through Transparency

- Always show data freshness
- Explain calculations simply
- Provide support access everywhere
- No hidden states or mystery

---

4. Information Architecture

4.1 Screen Hierarchy

```
App Root
|
+-- Onboarding (first-time only)
|   +-- Welcome
|   +-- Phone Verification
|   +-- Farmer Profile
|   +-- Plot Registration
|   +-- Sensor Pairing
|   +-- Setup Complete
|
+-- Main App (tab navigation)
|   |
|   +-- Home (default)
|   |   +-- Earnings Summary
|   |   +-- Plot Cards
|   |   +-- Quick Actions
|   |
|   +-- Plots
|   |   +-- Plot List
|   |   +-- Plot Detail
|   |   |   +-- Sensor Data
|   |   |   +-- Carbon Progress
|   |   |   +-- Activity Timeline
|   |   +-- Add Plot
|   |   +-- Edit Plot
|   |
|   +-- Earnings
|   |   +-- Summary
|   |   +-- Transaction History
|   |   +-- Transaction Detail
|   |   +-- Payout Settings
|   |
|   +-- Settings
|       +-- Profile
|       +-- Notifications
|       +-- Language
|       +-- Help & Support
|       +-- About
|       +-- Logout
|
+-- Overlays/Modals
|   +-- Verification Status
|   +-- Sensor Troubleshooting
|   +-- Alert Details
|   +-- Confirmation Dialogs
|
+-- Error States
    +-- Offline Mode
    +-- Sensor Error
    +-- Sync Error
    +-- Network Error
```

4.2 Navigation Model

Primary Navigation: Bottom tab bar (4 tabs)
- Home (house icon)
- Plots (plant/field icon)
- Earnings (euro/currency icon)
- Settings (gear icon)

Secondary Navigation: In-screen
- Back arrows for drilldown
- Pull-to-refresh for data update
- Floating action buttons for primary actions

