5. Screen-by-Screen Wireframes

5.1 Onboarding Flow

Screen 1.1: Welcome

Purpose: First impression, set expectations, language selection

Layout:
```
+----------------------------------+
|           [Status Bar]           |
+----------------------------------+
|                                  |
|                                  |
|         [GHL Logo - 80px]        |
|                                  |
|    "Earn from your hemp's        |
|     carbon capture"              |
|                                  |
|    [Illustration: Hemp field     |
|     with subtle CO2 arrows]      |
|                                  |
|                                  |
+----------------------------------+
|   [====== Get Started ======]    |  <- Primary Button
|                                  |
|   [Language: Francais    v]      |  <- Dropdown
|                                  |
|   "Already have account? Log in" |  <- Text Link
+----------------------------------+
```

Components:
- Logo: 80x80px centered
- Tagline: 24sp, centered, primary color
- Illustration: 200x150px, simple line art
- Primary button: Full width minus 32px padding, 56px height
- Language dropdown: 48px height, right-aligned flag icon

Copy (French):
- Tagline: "Gagnez de l'argent grace au carbone capte par votre chanvre"
- Button: "Commencer"
- Login link: "Deja un compte ? Se connecter"

Interactions:
- Tap "Get Started" -> Navigate to Phone Verification
- Tap language dropdown -> Show language picker modal
- Tap login link -> Navigate to login flow

---

Screen 1.2: Phone Verification

Purpose: Authenticate user via SMS, no passwords

Layout (Step 1 - Enter Phone):
```
+----------------------------------+
|  [<]        Phone Number         |
+----------------------------------+
|                                  |
|   Step 1 of 5                    |
|   [====-----------------]        |
|                                  |
|   "Enter your phone number"      |
|                                  |
|   We'll send you a code to       |
|   verify it's you.               |
|                                  |
|   +----+ +--------------------+  |
|   |+33 | |                    |  |
|   |[v] | | 6 12 34 56 78      |  |
|   +----+ +--------------------+  |
|                                  |
|                                  |
+----------------------------------+
|   [====== Send Code ======]      |
|                                  |
|   "By continuing, you agree to   |
|    our Terms and Privacy Policy" |
+----------------------------------+
```

Layout (Step 2 - Enter Code):
```
+----------------------------------+
|  [<]      Verification           |
+----------------------------------+
|                                  |
|   Step 1 of 5                    |
|   [====-----------------]        |
|                                  |
|   "Enter the 6-digit code"       |
|                                  |
|   Sent to +33 6 12 34 56 78      |
|                                  |
|   +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+  |
|   |  | |  | |  | |  | |  | |  |  |
|   +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+ +--+  |
|                                  |
|   Resend code (54s)              |
|                                  |
+----------------------------------+
|   [====== Verify ======]         |
|                                  |
|   "Didn't receive code?"         |
|    Call support: +33 X XX XX XX  |
+----------------------------------+
```

Components:
- Progress bar: 4px height, 20% filled
- Country code picker: 72px width, flag + code
- Phone input: Large numbers, 24sp, auto-format
- Code inputs: 6 separate boxes, 48x56px each
- Auto-advance on digit entry

Validation:
- Phone: Valid format for selected country
- Code: 6 digits, auto-submit when complete
- Rate limit: 3 attempts, then 60s cooldown

Error States:
- Invalid code: Shake animation, red border, "Code incorrect. Try again."
- Too many attempts: "Too many attempts. Try again in X minutes."
- Network error: "Can't send code. Check your connection."

