8. SMS Fallback System

8.1 SMS Message Templates

Earnings Notification
```
GHL: Vous avez gagne EUR 45.20 cette semaine. Total saison: EUR 1,247.50. 
Prochaine virement: 1er mars. Repondez AIDE pour assistance.

[English]
GHL: You earned EUR 45.20 this week. Season total: EUR 1,247.50. 
Next payout: March 1. Reply HELP for support.
```

Verification Complete
```
GHL: 2.1 tonnes de CO2 verifiees pour Parcelle Nord. 
EUR 31.50 sera credite. Voir details: ghl.earth/v/ABC123

[English]
GHL: 2.1 tonnes CO2 verified for Plot North. 
EUR 31.50 will be credited. View details: ghl.earth/v/ABC123
```

Payout Sent
```
GHL: EUR 245.00 envoye a votre compte bancaire 4567.
Reference: GHL-2026-0215. Questions? +33 3 25 92 31 92

[English]
GHL: EUR 245.00 sent to your bank account 4567.
Reference: GHL-2026-0215. Questions? +33 3 25 92 31 92
```

Sensor Alert
```
GHL: Alerte capteur Parcelle Nord - hors ligne depuis 24h. 
Verifiez les piles ou appelez +33 3 25 92 31 92 pour aide.

[English]
GHL: Sensor alert Plot North - offline for 24h. 
Check batteries or call +33 3 25 92 31 92 for help.
```

Action Required
```
GHL: Action requise: Confirmez la date de recolte pour Parcelle Nord. 
Appelez +33 3 25 92 31 92 ou visitez ghl.earth/confirm

[English]
GHL: Action required: Confirm harvest date for Plot North. 
Call +33 3 25 92 31 92 or visit ghl.earth/confirm
```

Weekly Summary
```
GHL Resume Hebdo: 2 parcelles actives, 4.2t CO2 capturees, 
EUR 63.00 en attente de verification. Bon travail!

[English]
GHL Weekly Summary: 2 plots active, 4.2t CO2 captured, 
EUR 63.00 pending verification. Good work!
```

8.2 SMS Response Handling

AIDE / HELP
```
Farmer sends: AIDE (or HELP)

Response:
GHL Support: Appelez +33 3 25 92 31 92 (Lun-Ven 9h-17h) ou 
envoyez votre question par SMS. Nous repondrons dans 24h.

[English]
GHL Support: Call +33 3 25 92 31 92 (Mon-Fri 9am-5pm) or 
send your question via SMS. We'll respond within 24h.
```

STOP
```
Farmer sends: STOP

Response:
GHL: Vous etes desinscrit des SMS. Reactivez dans l'app 
ou envoyez START. Alertes critiques resteront actives.

[English]
GHL: You've been unsubscribed from SMS. Reactivate in app 
or send START. Critical alerts will remain active.
```

START
```
Farmer sends: START

Response:
GHL: SMS reactives. Vous recevrez les alertes importantes 
et resumes hebdomadaires.

[English]
GHL: SMS reactivated. You'll receive important alerts 
and weekly summaries.
```

8.3 SMS Delivery Rules

| Notification Type | Push | SMS Fallback | SMS-Only Users |
|-------------------|------|--------------|----------------|
| Earnings weekly | Yes | If push fails | Yes |
| Verification complete | Yes | If push fails | Yes |
| Payout sent | Yes | Always | Yes |
| Sensor alert | Yes | If no response in 4h | Yes |
| Action required | Yes | If no response in 24h | Yes |

---

9. Accessibility Guidelines

9.1 Visual Accessibility

Color Contrast
- Text on backgrounds: Minimum 4.5:1 ratio (WCAG AA)
- Large text (18sp+): Minimum 3:1 ratio
- Interactive elements: Clearly distinguishable

Color Independence
- Never use color alone to convey meaning
- Status indicators: Color + icon + text
- Charts: Pattern fills in addition to colors

Text Scaling
- Support system font scaling up to 200%
- Test layouts at maximum scale
- Horizontal scrolling acceptable for data tables only

Screen Reader Support
- All images have contentDescription
- Touch targets have accessibility labels
- Reading order matches visual order
- Headings properly marked (accessibility headers)

9.2 Motor Accessibility

Touch Targets
- Minimum 48x48dp for all interactive elements
- Spacing: 8dp minimum between targets
- Gestures: Always provide tap alternative to swipe

Input Methods
- Support external keyboards
- Tab order logical and complete
- Focus indicators visible

9.3 Cognitive Accessibility

Simplicity
- One idea per screen
- Consistent navigation
- Predictable interactions
- Clear error recovery

Timing
- No time-limited actions
- Animations can be disabled
- Auto-logout with warning

Memory
- Don't require remembering info between screens
- Provide context on every screen
- Clear breadcrumbs/back navigation

---

10. Localization Notes

10.1 Supported Languages (Launch)

| Language | Code | Region | Notes |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| French | fr-FR | France | Primary, La Chanvriere |
| English | en-GB | UK/Intl | Fallback |
| German | de-DE | Germany | Large market |
| Dutch | nl-NL | Netherlands | HempFlax |

10.2 Text Expansion Guidelines

| Source (English) | French | German | Dutch |
|------------------|--------|--------|-------|
| 100% | +15-20% | +30% | +10% |

Design Implications:
- Buttons: Test with longest translation
- Labels: Allow 2 lines if needed
- Headers: Consider abbreviations

10.3 Number Formatting

| Locale | Number | Currency | Date |
|--------|--------|----------|------|
| fr-FR | 1 234,56 | 1 234,56 EUR | 15/02/2026 |
| en-GB | 1,234.56 | EUR 1,234.56 | 15/02/2026 |
| de-DE | 1.234,56 | 1.234,56 EUR | 15.02.2026 |
| nl-NL | 1.234,56 | EUR 1.234,56 | 15-02-2026 |

10.4 Cultural Considerations

French
- Formal "vous" throughout (not "tu")
- Full month names preferred
- Time: 24-hour format

German
- Formal "Sie" throughout
- Compound words may be very long
- Date format: dd.mm.yyyy

Dutch
- Formal "u" for initial contact
- Can switch to informal after rapport
- Direct communication style acceptable

10.5 String Management

- All strings externalized (no hardcoded text)
- Use ICU MessageFormat for plurals
- Include translator context comments
- Right-to-left: Not required for launch languages

---

11. Technical Requirements

11.1 Platform Specifications

iOS
- Minimum: iOS 14.0
- Target: iOS 17.0
- Devices: iPhone 8 and newer
- Required: Push notifications, Camera, Location, NFC

Android
- Minimum: API 29 (Android 10)
- Target: API 34 (Android 14)
- Devices: Phones with 720p+ screens
- Required: Push, Camera, Location, NFC

11.2 Performance Requirements

| Metric | Target | Maximum |
|--------|--------|---------|
| App launch (cold) | < 2s | 4s |
| App launch (warm) | < 500ms | 1s |
| Screen transition | < 300ms | 500ms |
| API response display | < 1s | 3s |
| Offline data load | < 200ms | 500ms |

11.3 Offline Capabilities

Data Cached Locally:
- User profile
- All plots and current status
- Last 30 days of transactions
- Sensor pairing information
- FAQ content

Queue for Sync:
- Plot updates (dates, name)
- Issue reports
- Settings changes

Not Available Offline:
- New plot registration (requires server validation)
- Sensor pairing (requires server handshake)
- Bank detail changes (security requirement)

11.4 Data Synchronization

- Background sync: Every 15 minutes when online
- Foreground sync: On app open, pull-to-refresh
- Conflict resolution: Server wins (last write)
- Sync indicator: Show "Syncing..." in header

11.5 Security Requirements

- All network traffic: TLS 1.3
- Local storage: Encrypted (iOS Keychain, Android EncryptedSharedPreferences)
- Session: JWT with 24h expiry, refresh token with 30d expiry
- Biometric: Optional for app unlock
- PIN: Optional fallback if biometric unavailable

11.6 Analytics Events

| Event | Parameters | Purpose |
|-------|------------|---------|
| onboarding_start | - | Funnel tracking |
| onboarding_step_complete | step_number, step_name | Drop-off analysis |
| onboarding_complete | duration_seconds | Success rate |
| plot_added | plot_size, has_sensor | Feature usage |
| earnings_viewed | - | Engagement |
| transaction_viewed | transaction_type | Interest tracking |
| sensor_alert_opened | alert_type | Support needs |
| support_contacted | method (chat/call/email) | Support volume |
| error_occurred | error_type, screen | Bug tracking |

---

